# AB Test — Skill Isolation Rule

This project runs a parallel A/B implementation experiment. Each agent MUST only use its assigned skill set.

## Agent A

- Branch: `feature/agent-a-implementation`
- Allowed skills: `.cursor/skills_A/` (discover, focus, build-ai, review, ship)
- Forbidden: `.cursor/skills_B/` — never read, reference, or use any skill from this folder

## Agent B

- Branch: `feature/agent-b-implementation`
- Allowed skills: `.cursor/skills_B/` (discover, focus, build-ai, review, ship)
- Forbidden: `.cursor/skills_A/` — never read, reference, or use any skill from this folder

## Shared Access (both agents)

- `/docs/kiotviet/` — translated KiotViet API documentation
- `/docs/` — any other shared documentation
- `/shared/` — shared utilities

## Enforcement

1. Before reading any skill, check the current git branch.
2. If on `feature/agent-a-implementation`, only read from `.cursor/skills_A/`.
3. If on `feature/agent-b-implementation`, only read from `.cursor/skills_B/`.
4. Implementation code, reasoning, and architecture decisions must stay isolated to each branch.
5. No cross-branch code sharing during the experiment.
